  "text": "The Firefox CSS layout engine reflow pipeline is implemented across multiple C++ source files organized in the mozilla/gecko-dev repository's layout directory.\n\n## Frame Construction\nThe frame construction subsystem is responsible for building the frame tree from the DOM tree. The primary implementation is in:\n- layout/base/nsCSSFrameConstructor.cpp/h: Main frame constructor class that implements the BeginUpdate/EndUpdate lifecycle and frame tree building algorithms.\n\n## Block Layout Reflow\nThe block layout reflow pipeline is the core of CSS layout for block-level elements:\n- layout/generic/ReflowInput.cpp/h: Reflow input parameters struct that contains all input to a reflow operation, including constrained width/height, margins, padding, and other state.\n- layout/generic/ReflowOutput.cpp/h: Reflow output struct that frames use to return their computed size and other metrics back to their parents.\n- layout/generic/BlockReflowState.cpp/h: State machine for block layout reflow, tracking line breaking and space management.\n- layout/generic/nsBlockFrame.cpp/h: Implementation of block frame reflow, the most common frame type for CSS blocks.\n- layout/generic/nsBlockReflowContext.cpp/h: Helper class for block reflow operations like sizing and placing block children.\n- layout/generic/nsBlockDebugFlags.h: Debug utilities for block layout.\n\n## Dirty-Frame Invalidation Mechanism\nThe dirty frame invalidation system marks frames that need reflow when style or content changes:\n- layout/generic/nsFrameStateBits.h: Bit flags for frame state including NS_FRAME_IS_DIRTY and NS_FRAME_HAS_DIRTY_CHILDREN which are the core dirty bits.\n- layout/generic/nsFrameState.cpp/h: Management of frame state bits.\n- layout/base/nsFrameManager.cpp/h: Frame manager that tracks the frame tree and handles frame changes.\n- layout/style/nsChangeHint.h: Change hint flags that indicate what layout/style updates are needed (reflow, repaint, etc.).\n- layout/style/nsStyleChangeList.cpp/h: List of elements that have changed and their change hints.\n- layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp/h: Manages style tree changes and propagates dirty bits through the frame tree.\n- layout/painting/nsDisplayListInvalidation.cpp/h: Display list invalidation tracking when visual properties change.\n\n## Frame Base Classes\nAll frame types inherit from base classes that define the reflow interface:\n- layout/generic/nsIFrame.cpp/h: The main nsIFrame base class defining Reflow(), DidReflow(), and other frame lifecycle methods.\n- layout/generic/nsContainerFrame.cpp/h: Base class for frames that have children.\n- layout/generic/nsLeafFrame.cpp/h: Base class for frames without children.\n- layout/generic/nsAtomicContainerFrame.h: Atomic container frame for non-splittable containers.\n\n## Inline Layout\nInline layout is handled separately and is critical for text and inline element layout:\n- layout/generic/nsInlineFrame.cpp/h: Inline frame implementation.\n- layout/generic/nsLineLayout.cpp/h: Line layout engine for inline content.\n- layout/generic/nsLineBox.cpp/h: Line box structure representing a line in inline layout.\n\n## Frame Tree Management\n- layout/generic/nsFrameList.cpp/h: Doubly-linked list of frames.\n- layout/base/FrameProperties.h: Property storage for frame objects.\n- layout/base/DepthOrderedFrameList.cpp/h: Depth-ordered list for efficient frame traversal.\n\n## Reflow Orchestration\n- layout/base/PresShell.cpp/h: Presentation shell that orchestrates the reflow process, manages FrameNeedsReflow bits, and coordinates with the refresh driver.\n- layout/base/nsPresContext.cpp/h: Presentation context managing document layout state.\n- layout/base/nsRefreshDriver.cpp/h: Refresh driver that schedules and executes reflow.\n\n## Display List & Visual Invalidation\n- layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp/h: Display list for painting and visual updates.\n- layout/painting/nsDisplayListInvalidation.cpp/h: Tracks display list changes for invalidation.\n\n## Special Layout Modules\n- layout/generic/AbsoluteContainingBlock.cpp/h: Absolute positioning layout.\n- layout/generic/ViewportFrame.cpp/h: Root viewport frame.\n- layout/generic/nsPageFrame.cpp/h and layout/generic/nsPageContentFrame.cpp/h: Page layout for print/pagination.\n- layout/generic/nsCanvasFrame.cpp: Root frame for HTML documents.\n- layout/generic/ScrollContainerFrame.cpp/h: Scrollable container frames.\n- layout/generic/nsFlexContainerFrame.cpp: Flexbox layout.\n- layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp: CSS Grid layout.\n- layout/generic/nsColumnSetFrame.cpp/h and layout/generic/ColumnSetWrapperFrame.cpp/h: Multi-column layout.\n- layout/generic/nsPlaceholderFrame.cpp/h: Placeholder frames for positioned elements.\n- layout/generic/nsSplittableFrame.cpp/h: Splittable frames for multi-page content.\n- layout/generic/nsFirstLetterFrame.cpp/h: First-letter pseudo-element frames.\n- layout/generic/nsFrameSetFrame.cpp/h: HTML frameset layout.\n\n## Utilities & Helpers\n- layout/base/nsIReflowCallback.h: Callback interface for post-reflow notifications.\n- layout/base/nsAutoLayoutPhase.cpp/h: RAII helper for layout phase management.\n- layout/base/OverflowChangedTracker.h: Tracks overflow changes that require reflow.\n\nTogether, these files implement the complete CSS layout engine pipeline: frame construction from the DOM, reflow calculation through the frame tree, and dirty-frame invalidation tracking that marks frames needing relayout when the document changes."
}

